    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Augsburg, 9 March 1551)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Gergely Bornemissza, George Martinuzzi’s legate, has
                            handed over Oláh’s letter. Bornemissza has come to Augsburg and
                            presented what had been entrusted to him. Since King Ferdinand I wants
                            to be in Vienna within eight days, he has postponed the legate’s matter
                            until then to think about the answer. He will let Oláh know so Oláh can
                            be there when he arrives.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime Fidelis nobis Dilecte! </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Reddidit nobis litteras<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">We do not
                        know this letter.</note> Devotionis Tuae <persName>Gregorius
                        Bornemissa</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Gergely
                        Bornemissza.</note> nuntius reverendissimi <persName>episcopi
                        Waradiensis</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">George
                        Martinuzzi.</note> qui hodie huc <placeName>Augustam</placeName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Augsburg.</note> applicuit, nosque <del
                        corresp="scriba">tamen</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">primum</add> a
                    meridie inter secundam et tertiam horam convenit et mandata sua nobis exposuit.
                    Cum utro <del corresp="scriba"> cras discessivi</del> cras discedere et intra
                    octiduum <placeName>Viennam</placeName> dante Deo pervenire statuerimus, eiusdem
                    nuntii expeditionem eo usque differendam esse censuimus, ut illis omnibus <del
                        corresp="scriba">maturius deliberare</del> ponderitis <del corresp="scriba"
                        >eo</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">tanto</add> melius respondere, et
                    deinde ipsum nuntium, quem <del corresp="scriba">eo etiamsi</del> pro nunc eo
                    remisimus, recta ad ipsum <persName>Waradiensem</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">Martinuzzi was also Bishop of Oradea.</note><del
                        corresp="scriba">ac remittere</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >expedire</add> possimus. Quod <del corresp="scriba">tibi</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">Devotioni Tuae</add> ideo significamus, ut in
                    adventu istic nostro <del corresp="scriba">nobis tu</del> Devotio Tua quoque ibi
                    adsit. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Datum <placeName>Augustae</placeName> die 9. Martii 1551.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Agriensi.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
